  <bioghist id="aspace_9aadaf8f05e71eb6c00e7fddfa9fb14a">
    <head>BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE</head>
<p>City planner Nelson P. Lewis served as chief engineer of Brooklyn, New York from 1902-1920. He wrote <title>The Planning of the Modern City</title>, 1916. In May 1921 he became Director of the Physical Survey of the Regional Plan of New York and Its Environs.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_a6b4c61f757d374b24d5ee29fb40fd3e">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Speeches and papers given by Nelson P. Lewis; scrapbooks of news clippings and programs, 1896-1923; scrapbook of reviews of <title>The Planning of the Modern City</title>, 1919-1923; professional engineering license, 1921; three illuminated memorial booklets, 1924; copies of <title>The Planning of the Modern City</title>, 1916; <title>Urbanizacion</title>, the Spanish edition, 1917-1918; and other books by Nelson P. Lewis.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <prefercite id="aspace_a6101fa99e9945ce70b8576a4d8e66be">
    <head>Cite As:</head>
<p>Nelson Peter Lewis Papers, #2712. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.</p>  </prefercite>
